THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 392.4637 is hereby amended to read as
2 follows:
3 392.4637 1. The board of trustees of each school district shall
4 adopt a policy concerning the use and possession by pupils of [a
5 pager, cellular telephone or any other similar] an electronic
6 communication device [used for communication] while on the
7 premises of a public school or while at an activity sponsored by a
8 public school.
9 2. The policy adopted pursuant to subsection 1 must:
10 (a) Prescribe appropriate measures for disciplining a pupil who
11 violates the policy [.] that include, without limitation, a system to
12 rate violations of a policy adopted pursuant to subsection 1 on a
13 progressive scale based on the number and seriousness of the
14 violations.
15 (b) Prescribe limitations on the use of an electronic
16 communication device during instruction.
17 (c) Include exceptions to any limitations on the use of an
18 electronic communication device prescribed as part of a policy
19 adopted pursuant to subsection 1, including, without limitation,
20 exceptions:
21 (1) On the use of an electronic communication device
22 during an emergency or crisis or to manage the health of a pupil;
23 (2) If a teacher allows for the use of an electronic
24 communication device for instructional purposes; and
25 (3) If the use of an electronic communication device is
26 included as part of an individualized education program or a plan
27 developed in accordance with section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act
28 of 1973, 29 U.S.C. § 794.
29 (d) Be included within each copy of the rules of behavior
30 for pupils that the school district provides to pupils pursuant to
31 NRS 392.463.
32 3. As used in this section:
33 (a) “Electronic communication device” means any electronic
34 device that is capable of transmitting any audio, written or
35 pictorial information or messages to another electronic device.
36 The term includes, without limitation, a cellular phone, computer,
37 laptop computer and tablet device. The term does not include an
38 electronic device issued to a pupil by the school district or the
39 school in which the pupil is enrolled.
40 (b) “Individualized education program” has the meaning
41 ascribed to it in 20 U.S.C. § 1414(d)(1)(A).
42 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective:
